header file - string

string s1 -----> intializes the string

getline(cin , s1) ---------> thats how u input the string using cin function

s1.compare(s2) ------> compares the string
if s1 > = s2 -ve number
s1 = s2 = 0
s2 > s1 = +ve number

s1.erase( {the postion of the element} , {number of charachters u want to erase })
for ex
s1 = "Saaransh";
s1.erase(3,2) then,
s1 = Saansh
element at 3rd index = r so 2 charachters after r is deleted

s1.append({string u want to append})
for ex
s1="Saar" ;
s2="ansh" ;
s1.append(s2); then
s1 = Saaransh 

u can also do
s1 = s1 + s2 ;
to append 

s1.find({the substring or charachter u want to find in the string})
for ex
s1 = "Saaransh"
s1.find("ans")
= 4

s1.insert({locate at which index you want to insert , string u want to insert})
for ex 
s1 = saransh ;
s1.insert(2,a) ;
= saaransh

s1.length() or s1.size() ----> gives the length of the string

s1.substr({index} , {number of letters})
for ex
s1 = saaransh
s1.substr(2,3);
=ara

stoi(s1) ----> it converts the string into integer if the string is of integers ;
for ex
s1 = "786" ;
int x = stoi(s1) ;
x = 786

to_string -----> converts integer into string
for ex
int x = 786 ;
string s1 = to_string(x);
s1 = "786" 

sort(starting point, ending point) -----> sorts the string alphabetically
USES HEADER FILE = algorithm
#include<algorithm>

for ex
s1 = "zxy" ;
sort(s1.begin() , s1.end())
//s1.begin() gives the starting point of the string
//s1.end() gives the index next to end of the string
s1 = xyz 